HEADWORD: Deltohedron
<hw>Del`to*he"dron</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>de`lta</grk>, the letter ⟦DELTA⟧ + <grk>'e`dra</grk> seat,
base.]</ety> <fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>A solid bounded by twelve
quadrilateral faces. It is a hemihedral form of the isometric system,
allied to the tetrahedron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deltoid</ent>⟦br⟧
